1
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,760
<i>Mr. Rut Rueangwichan</i>

2
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:45,440
<i>is currently on the run. If you spot him,</i>

3
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:48,440
<i>I'll reward you immediately in cash,</i>
<i>100,000 baht.</i>

4
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:52,040
You think your money is God or what?

5
00:02:52,120 --> 00:02:54,040
Our customers'
personal info database got hacked.

6
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:55,160
They're threatening

7
00:02:55,240 --> 00:02:57,320
to keep releasing customer data bit by bit

8
00:02:57,400 --> 00:02:59,080
if we don't pay them 100 million baht.

9
00:02:59,160 --> 00:03:00,520
100 million?

10
00:03:00,600 --> 00:03:03,040
Your life with Trai will never be peaceful

11
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:05,040
if you let him roam free like this.

12
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:06,760
Let's work together.

13
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:13,280
Pakbung?!

14
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:18,520
<i>Then I'll blow you up.</i>

15
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:20,400
Both your hearts will merge together.

16
00:03:24,640 --> 00:03:25,880
No…

17
00:03:25,960 --> 00:03:27,280
- No.
- Don't, Rut, don't!

18
00:03:28,440 --> 00:03:29,480
Don't!

19
00:03:29,920 --> 00:03:30,920
Don't!

20
00:03:32,480 --> 00:03:34,640
Uncle Rat, if you meet Rut,
please tell him

21
00:03:34,720 --> 00:03:36,680
I forgive him.

22
00:03:36,760 --> 00:03:38,480
May he rest in peace,

23
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:40,440
and may we no longer hold
any grudges against each other.

24
00:04:13,240 --> 00:04:15,520
Our school is an alternative school

25
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:18,560
focused on children's
holistic development,

26
00:04:18,640 --> 00:04:20,279
physically,

27
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:22,520
mentally, emotionally, socially,

28
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:24,680
and intellectually.

29
00:04:25,440 --> 00:04:27,760
We let children learn

30
00:04:27,840 --> 00:04:30,320
through fun activities,
both in the classroom

31
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:31,600
and in the garden,

32
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:34,040
because play and hands-on experiences

33
00:04:34,120 --> 00:04:36,240
help create better learning outcomes.

34
00:04:47,080 --> 00:04:50,520
I can assure you,
your children will learn in two languages

35
00:04:51,160 --> 00:04:53,160
at the same tuition fee.

36
00:04:54,320 --> 00:04:56,280
Teacher Nam

37
00:04:56,360 --> 00:04:58,840
will now take everyone
on a tour around the school.

38
00:04:59,560 --> 00:05:00,640
Please take care of them.

39
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:21,400
I heard you had been discharged
from the hospital.

40
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:25,080
I'm sorry I could only visit a few times.

41
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:28,320
It's okay. You've been busy.

42
00:05:30,360 --> 00:05:32,920
So, when does the school open?

43
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:35,480
In about a month.

44
00:05:37,040 --> 00:05:38,280
Ms. Darin, did you want
to talk about something?

45
00:05:38,360 --> 00:05:39,640
Of course.

46
00:05:40,280 --> 00:05:41,480
Otherwise, I wouldn't be here.

47
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:44,360
I'm going to get ordained.

48
00:05:44,440 --> 00:05:45,480
Huh?

49
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:48,680
Not shaving my head.
Just becoming a white-robed nun.

50
00:05:48,760 --> 00:05:52,120
I think I'll go for a week.
I'm going with my mom.

51
00:05:52,760 --> 00:05:55,600
I see. So,

52
00:05:55,680 --> 00:05:58,600
should I rejoice in your merit now?

53
00:05:58,680 --> 00:06:01,240
I wanted to ask
for your forgiveness first.

54
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:03,440
I'm sorry, Pakbung,

55
00:06:04,200 --> 00:06:06,160
for anything I've ever done wrong to you.

56
00:06:07,640 --> 00:06:08,960
Well…

57
00:06:09,840 --> 00:06:10,840
I…

58
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:13,040
wasn't exactly kind to you either.

59
00:06:15,960 --> 00:06:17,600
I'm sorry too.

60
00:06:21,880 --> 00:06:23,480
I used to think

61
00:06:23,560 --> 00:06:27,600
you were lucky to have met Trai
after he had changed for the better.

62
00:06:27,680 --> 00:06:29,560
But thinking about it,

63
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:31,080
without you,

64
00:06:31,680 --> 00:06:33,280
Trai wouldn't be who he is today.

65
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:38,640
He's the lucky one
to love someone like you.

66
00:06:45,440 --> 00:06:48,320
Please take good care of this love.

67
00:06:48,400 --> 00:06:50,800
And I truly hope you'll be very happy.

68
00:06:51,520 --> 00:06:52,960
Thank you.

69
00:06:53,880 --> 00:06:56,760
Alright, I won't disturb you anymore.
I'll get going.

70
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:00,880
Ms. Darin.

71
00:07:03,600 --> 00:07:05,160
Are you free this evening?

72
00:07:06,320 --> 00:07:08,200
- Yes. That's how it should be.
- It's burning.

73
00:07:08,280 --> 00:07:10,640
Put it on my plate. On my plate.

74
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:13,440
No, get it yourself.

75
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:15,440
Ms. Darin, you can sit here.

76
00:07:16,280 --> 00:07:17,320
Okay.

77
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:25,720
Hey.

78
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:28,200
I know you two made up,
but you aren't that close.

79
00:07:28,280 --> 00:07:29,960
Why did you bring her here?

80
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:32,720
So there would be more people
to share the cost.

81
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:33,760
Alright.

82
00:07:34,280 --> 00:07:35,240
Let's go.

83
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:41,560
Kanah,

84
00:07:41,640 --> 00:07:43,720
get her a bowl and chopsticks.

85
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:45,760
Sure.

86
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:53,120
Here you go. Right here.

87
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:55,920
Thank you.

88
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:57,640
Bung told me

89
00:07:57,720 --> 00:08:00,080
you helped when she fought Rut.

90
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:09,200
Ah, excuse me.

91
00:08:09,280 --> 00:08:11,600
Here, this one's ready.

92
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:13,760
It's perfect.

93
00:08:13,840 --> 00:08:16,400
Here. Dip it in this sauce.

94
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,920
Then take this too.

95
00:08:19,520 --> 00:08:21,280
Shrimp! So you'll get nice and plump.

96
00:08:21,360 --> 00:08:24,960
- Who gains weight from shrimp?
- I gave her the bigger piece.

97
00:08:25,040 --> 00:08:27,680
- Who gains weight from it?
- This one too.

98
00:08:27,760 --> 00:08:29,240
- That's enough.
- Oh? What about mine?

99
00:08:29,320 --> 00:08:30,680
Get it yourself.

100
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:32,080
The papaya salad is good too.

101
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:34,520
- Yes.
- How is that?

102
00:08:34,600 --> 00:08:37,400
Oh, you already started?
You didn't wait for us?

103
00:08:37,480 --> 00:08:38,880
We were waiting, Trai.

104
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:40,720
I saved you a whole tray of pork.

105
00:08:40,799 --> 00:08:41,600
Just one tray?

106
00:08:41,679 --> 00:08:43,880
If it's not enough, just order more.

107
00:08:43,960 --> 00:08:45,880
Mr. Rachen is here.
What's there to worry about?

108
00:08:47,080 --> 00:08:48,040
Hold on.

109
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:50,760
If I'm paying,
there has to be something in exchange.

110
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:53,520
How about my body and heart?

111
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:54,840
Is that enough?

112
00:08:56,480 --> 00:08:58,360
Enough. Enough out of you.

113
00:08:58,440 --> 00:08:59,600
Let's go eat.

114
00:08:59,680 --> 00:09:00,760
I'm hungry. So hungry.

115
00:09:00,840 --> 00:09:03,520
- Ugh, you again.
- Let's go.

116
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:04,840
- Calm down.
- Give them plates.

117
00:09:04,920 --> 00:09:05,840
Bring the plates.

118
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:06,960
- Plates.
- Hello.

119
00:09:07,040 --> 00:09:07,880
You always steal my food.

120
00:09:07,960 --> 00:09:10,040
- Yeah, get us plates.
- Get us plates.

121
00:09:11,160 --> 00:09:12,760
I didn't expect you to be here.

122
00:09:14,440 --> 00:09:16,720
I'm also surprised to see you here.

123
00:09:17,320 --> 00:09:19,560
Why surprised?
The pork BBQ here is the best.

124
00:09:19,640 --> 00:09:20,520
How could I not come?

125
00:09:23,160 --> 00:09:24,520
- Hey!
- Hey, Kanah!

126
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:26,960
It's all over my back!

127
00:09:27,040 --> 00:09:28,440
Whoa! My back.

128
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:31,800
- It's all over the place.
- Right.

129
00:09:31,880 --> 00:09:34,440
I now know
why Trai likes this place so much.

130
00:09:35,480 --> 00:09:36,680
Because it's this good.

131
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:40,920
- Too hot?
- Yes. Blow on it for me.

132
00:09:43,840 --> 00:09:45,480
Get a cup.

133
00:09:46,040 --> 00:09:47,360
- Samlee. Kanah.
- Yes?

134
00:09:49,320 --> 00:09:50,320
It's good now.

135
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:53,280
Come.

136
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:55,320
Eat more.

137
00:09:55,400 --> 00:09:58,840
With a mood like this,
all sweet like this,

138
00:09:58,920 --> 00:10:01,200
shouldn't someone do something?

139
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:03,960
Propose!

140
00:10:05,080 --> 00:10:11,080
Propose! Propose!

141
00:10:11,160 --> 00:10:13,440
What are you waiting for, Mr. Trai?

142
00:10:13,520 --> 00:10:14,600
Propose now.

143
00:10:14,680 --> 00:10:16,120
Propose! Propose!

144
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:19,360
Propose! Propose!

145
00:10:19,440 --> 00:10:20,520
Propose. Propose.

146
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:23,360
You're crazy. Propose what?

147
00:10:24,400 --> 00:10:26,560
- Hey, hey.
- What? What?

148
00:10:26,640 --> 00:10:28,040
What's that?

149
00:10:31,640 --> 00:10:32,960
I do want to marry you, Pakbung.

150
00:10:38,160 --> 00:10:39,440
But not right now.

151
00:10:41,920 --> 00:10:43,360
Not right now? So,

152
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:44,760
it will be soon, right?

153
00:10:44,840 --> 00:10:46,960
That's right. Soon.
Just wait a little more.

154
00:10:47,040 --> 00:10:49,720
- Yes.
- He'll propose.

155
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:52,400
- Just wait.
- Yeah.

156
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:55,000
- It won't be long.
- Yeah.

157
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:56,360
- She can wait.
- Eat up.

158
00:10:56,440 --> 00:10:57,640
Bacon.

159
00:10:59,080 --> 00:11:00,400
Thank you.

160
00:11:05,720 --> 00:11:06,560
Pakbung…

161
00:11:07,960 --> 00:11:09,720
I know what you're going to say.

162
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:13,920
I understand. I really do.

163
00:11:14,720 --> 00:11:15,680
Understand what?

164
00:11:17,560 --> 00:11:20,360
I understand that Be Rich is in trouble.

165
00:11:20,440 --> 00:11:22,640
You want to go back
and help Mr. Rachen fix it

166
00:11:22,720 --> 00:11:24,480
because Mr. Tritot

167
00:11:24,560 --> 00:11:26,480
entrusted Be Rich to you.

168
00:11:29,560 --> 00:11:30,960
You really know me.

169
00:11:32,760 --> 00:11:33,600
No.

170
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:36,880
You really understand me.

171
00:11:38,880 --> 00:11:41,520
If I can't even understand
something like this,

172
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:43,760
how are we supposed
to walk forward together?

173
00:11:44,480 --> 00:11:45,760
Right?

174
00:11:48,320 --> 00:11:49,720
If you're this cute,

175
00:11:50,920 --> 00:11:52,680
you deserve a prize, don't you think?

176
00:11:58,240 --> 00:12:00,600
The important thing is

177
00:12:01,520 --> 00:12:03,720
if you abandon Be Rich and choose me,

178
00:12:04,240 --> 00:12:08,200
then my future
as a rich man's wife is over.

179
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:09,800
I'm not agreeing to that.

180
00:12:11,440 --> 00:12:14,600
And we're back to money again.
I was having a heartfelt moment.

181
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:23,240
Mr. Trai.

182
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:30,360
Take your time dealing with your problems.

183
00:12:30,440 --> 00:12:33,360
I'm not in a rush. I'm not going anywhere.

184
00:12:33,960 --> 00:12:36,560
You waited for me to be ready for so long.

185
00:12:36,640 --> 00:12:40,320
Why can't I be
the one waiting for you this time? Right?

186
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:46,560
I'll settle Be Rich as soon as possible,

187
00:12:50,160 --> 00:12:52,720
so you can become my wife sooner.
Sound good?

188
00:12:55,440 --> 00:12:56,400
Are you crazy?

189
00:12:57,160 --> 00:12:59,000
It's not like I even want to be your wife.

190
00:12:59,880 --> 00:13:00,800
You don't?

191
00:13:02,360 --> 00:13:03,600
I do.

192
00:13:06,280 --> 00:13:07,480
Let's go.

193
00:13:14,440 --> 00:13:16,480
I intend to revive Be Rich

194
00:13:17,120 --> 00:13:19,600
by rebranding our corporate image.

195
00:13:20,760 --> 00:13:22,280
We'll become a loan company

196
00:13:22,360 --> 00:13:24,960
that helps the poor and is friendly
toward the underprivileged.

197
00:13:25,040 --> 00:13:27,160
I've prepared a proposal
for everyone to review.

198
00:13:28,160 --> 00:13:29,200
Trai,

199
00:13:29,280 --> 00:13:31,320
we're not trying to become a charity.

200
00:13:31,400 --> 00:13:33,080
We want profits.

201
00:13:33,160 --> 00:13:34,160
Exactly.

202
00:13:34,240 --> 00:13:35,560
And we're facing crisis after crisis.

203
00:13:35,640 --> 00:13:39,560
Focus on saving the company
before thinking about helping others.

204
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:45,160
Rebranding is exactly
how we'll overcome this crisis.

205
00:13:46,640 --> 00:13:48,560
Enough. This is a waste of time.

206
00:13:48,640 --> 00:13:50,480
You're an outsider.

207
00:13:50,560 --> 00:13:54,360
Honestly, you shouldn't even be
in this board meeting.

208
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:02,360
Trai, there's one way
you can help Be Rich right now.

209
00:14:05,320 --> 00:14:06,640
Go home for now.

210
00:14:09,760 --> 00:14:11,720
If you don't agree with my idea, fine.

211
00:14:11,800 --> 00:14:13,800
But why kick me out like that?

212
00:14:15,160 --> 00:14:17,120
You made it look like
I'm really an outsider.

213
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:22,640
Are you returning my shares or not?

214
00:14:23,680 --> 00:14:25,440
Listen carefully, Trai.

215
00:14:26,920 --> 00:14:28,480
In this world,

216
00:14:28,560 --> 00:14:30,320
being a good person isn't enough.

217
00:14:30,840 --> 00:14:32,520
You also need money.

218
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:34,920
If you really want to help

219
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:36,560
and change Be Rich,

220
00:14:36,640 --> 00:14:38,440
what you need to do is

221
00:14:38,520 --> 00:14:40,960
revise your plan so it generates

222
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:43,360
enough profit for the company
to keep growing.

223
00:14:45,760 --> 00:14:47,840
If I revise it

224
00:14:47,920 --> 00:14:51,000
and present it again to the board,

225
00:14:51,080 --> 00:14:53,200
will you return my shares?

226
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:56,720
Only if you can make
every board member accept you.

227
00:15:06,680 --> 00:15:08,240
Mr. Lee said

228
00:15:08,320 --> 00:15:10,760
Mr. Rachen won't return
the shares to Mr. Trai

229
00:15:10,840 --> 00:15:13,520
and even added new conditions.

230
00:15:13,600 --> 00:15:15,760
At this rate,
when are you going to get married to him?

231
00:15:17,400 --> 00:15:19,080
Whenever.

232
00:15:19,760 --> 00:15:20,800
I'm not in a rush.

233
00:15:22,200 --> 00:15:23,920
Maybe you should be.

234
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:26,520
People's hearts can change anytime.

235
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:29,600
If it's going to change,

236
00:15:31,360 --> 00:15:33,800
even marriage won't stop it.

237
00:15:34,320 --> 00:15:37,240
Marriage doesn't guarantee loyalty

238
00:15:37,320 --> 00:15:42,080
and doesn't guarantee lasting love.

239
00:15:42,960 --> 00:15:46,280
But if you don't marry him
and you break up,

240
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:49,440
you won't get any of Mr. Trai's assets.

241
00:15:52,320 --> 00:15:54,400
Right. That's something to think about.

242
00:15:56,880 --> 00:15:58,840
Can you two stop joking?

243
00:15:59,560 --> 00:16:01,680
Pakbung, listen to me.

244
00:16:01,760 --> 00:16:04,160
I'm not rushing you to get married.

245
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:06,920
But think about it. If you stay like this,

246
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:08,480
attached but not committed,

247
00:16:09,200 --> 00:16:11,000
one day,

248
00:16:11,080 --> 00:16:14,480
you might go from girlfriend
to just friend-zoned.

249
00:16:23,400 --> 00:16:24,800
Friend-zoned?

250
00:16:46,920 --> 00:16:48,760
Is Mr. Trai going to dump me?

251
00:17:15,160 --> 00:17:16,480
I missed you.

252
00:17:17,400 --> 00:17:19,599
Mr. Trai! What are you doing?

253
00:17:23,880 --> 00:17:24,880
Just finished work?

254
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:26,200
Not yet.

255
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:28,200
I just came to recharge a bit.

256
00:17:29,320 --> 00:17:30,160
Recharge?

257
00:17:31,640 --> 00:17:33,640
Hey.

258
00:17:33,720 --> 00:17:36,120
Can I carry you back to work with me?

259
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:37,720
I'd get unlimited energy.

260
00:17:38,800 --> 00:17:40,440
I charge for energy refills.

261
00:17:40,520 --> 00:17:41,640
How much?

262
00:17:44,240 --> 00:17:45,640
Acting like a big spender now?

263
00:17:45,720 --> 00:17:49,520
You're weird.
Usually, you don't even ask the price.

264
00:17:49,600 --> 00:17:51,160
Because I missed you.

265
00:17:51,960 --> 00:17:53,000
You're tired, right?

266
00:17:54,200 --> 00:17:55,160
I'm spent.

267
00:18:03,640 --> 00:18:06,200
It's not physical exhaustion, it's stress.

268
00:18:08,360 --> 00:18:10,480
Everything my dad forced me to learn,

269
00:18:11,120 --> 00:18:12,760
I'm using it all now.

270
00:18:13,640 --> 00:18:16,240
Sometimes, I get mad at myself
for not having listened to him back then.

271
00:18:18,040 --> 00:18:19,640
You were young.

272
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:22,760
Young and stubborn.

273
00:18:23,680 --> 00:18:25,520
So what does a stubborn kid deserve?

274
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:27,360
Huh?

275
00:18:28,360 --> 00:18:30,120
Can you punish this stubborn kid?

276
00:18:33,120 --> 00:18:33,960
Sure.

277
00:18:35,200 --> 00:18:36,120
Close your eyes.

278
00:18:43,160 --> 00:18:44,040
Pakbung. That hurts.

279
00:18:44,880 --> 00:18:46,840
What if I get brain damage?

280
00:18:48,320 --> 00:18:49,520
You told me to punish you.

281
00:18:50,480 --> 00:18:52,000
Punishment should be like this.

282
00:19:18,920 --> 00:19:21,120
I have to get back to work. I'm going.

283
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:34,000
Wait, Mr. Trai.

284
00:19:34,560 --> 00:19:36,680
Mr. Trai.

285
00:19:36,760 --> 00:19:39,400
Hey. Wait.

286
00:19:42,240 --> 00:19:43,800
What was that?

287
00:19:44,680 --> 00:19:46,560
- I punished myself.
- Huh?

288
00:19:46,640 --> 00:19:50,120
Listen. If I hadn't stopped,
things would've gone further.

289
00:19:50,200 --> 00:19:52,120
So I held myself back.

290
00:19:52,200 --> 00:19:54,320
That's the punishment I deserve.

291
00:19:56,480 --> 00:19:59,120
That feels more like punishing me.

292
00:20:00,360 --> 00:20:02,520
How can you tease me and just walk away?

293
00:20:23,280 --> 00:20:24,160
That's enough.

294
00:20:24,760 --> 00:20:26,120
Pakbung…

295
00:20:26,200 --> 00:20:29,840
This is real punishment.

296
00:20:31,160 --> 00:20:32,560
If you want more,

297
00:20:32,640 --> 00:20:37,000
go fix your problems first,
then come back and properly propose.

298
00:20:38,080 --> 00:20:40,720
Pakbung. Pakbung.

299
00:20:41,560 --> 00:20:42,560
Pakbung.

300
00:20:50,840 --> 00:20:53,440
And that's Be Rich, Be Happy.

301
00:20:54,320 --> 00:20:56,560
Money can buy many kinds of happiness,

302
00:20:56,640 --> 00:20:59,560
but not everything
can be bought with money.

303
00:21:00,960 --> 00:21:01,800
So, what do you all think?

304
00:21:26,280 --> 00:21:27,680
I did it, Bro.

305
00:21:28,840 --> 00:21:30,960
The board accepted my plan.

306
00:21:31,040 --> 00:21:33,440
Don't forget
what you promised me about the shares.

307
00:21:34,560 --> 00:21:35,960
When did I ever promise you that?

308
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:39,240
Are you cheating me?

309
00:21:39,320 --> 00:21:40,920
Cheat?

310
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:42,840
You transferred them to me yourself.

311
00:21:42,920 --> 00:21:44,560
No contract, no agreement.

312
00:21:44,640 --> 00:21:46,920
Only trust

313
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:48,960
won't keep you alive in business, Trai.

314
00:21:50,080 --> 00:21:51,240
You've gotta be more careful.

315
00:21:51,320 --> 00:21:53,560
But what you're doing right now
is being cunning.

316
00:21:53,640 --> 00:21:55,440
Can't help it.

317
00:21:55,520 --> 00:21:57,080
I've got more experience.

318
00:21:57,680 --> 00:22:00,160
- So this is what you're really like?
- I'm smarter than you.

319
00:22:00,240 --> 00:22:01,480
You asshole!

320
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:09,040
The share transfer documents
for Mr. Trai are here.

321
00:22:13,800 --> 00:22:16,960
Once you've read everything,
you can sign where I marked.

322
00:22:30,720 --> 00:22:32,280
So you were messing with me?

323
00:22:33,360 --> 00:22:36,360
Told you. I'm way smarter than you.

324
00:22:40,160 --> 00:22:41,600
But I'm more handsome than you.

325
00:22:44,680 --> 00:22:45,880
Your tie's a mess now.

326
00:23:00,440 --> 00:23:02,760
If I really hadn't returned your shares,
what would you have done?

327
00:23:03,680 --> 00:23:05,720
No idea.
Light incense and tell Dad, I guess.

328
00:23:07,520 --> 00:23:09,120
If you don't mess with me for once,
will you die or something?

329
00:23:11,320 --> 00:23:13,920
But honestly,
if you want Be Rich, just take it.

330
00:23:14,960 --> 00:23:17,240
I believe you'll take good care of it,

331
00:23:17,760 --> 00:23:18,760
just like Dad hoped.

332
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:20,600
That's such a hero line.

333
00:23:22,600 --> 00:23:24,400
But if you actually did that,

334
00:23:25,720 --> 00:23:27,120
you'd be hurting yourself.

335
00:23:27,200 --> 00:23:30,200
You'd spend your life with nothing
but work, nothing but money, no family,

336
00:23:30,280 --> 00:23:32,640
and no adorable little brother like me.

337
00:23:37,840 --> 00:23:40,920
Pakbung once told me, when we're up high,

338
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:43,000
all our problems look smaller.

339
00:23:43,920 --> 00:23:45,120
I thought that too.

340
00:23:45,200 --> 00:23:47,400
That's why I kept trying
to climb higher and higher.

341
00:23:47,480 --> 00:23:50,840
But in the end, it's the same everywhere.

342
00:23:52,880 --> 00:23:54,480
Misery doesn't care where you are.

343
00:23:56,560 --> 00:23:59,840
But there's one place that's safe.

344
00:24:00,760 --> 00:24:02,640
Not high, not low,

345
00:24:04,360 --> 00:24:06,320
just being surrounded
by the people you love.

346
00:24:13,760 --> 00:24:15,080
I'm glad

347
00:24:15,800 --> 00:24:17,160
we made it here.

348
00:24:22,360 --> 00:24:23,200
Me too.

349
00:24:27,720 --> 00:24:29,320
Love you, Big Bro.

350
00:24:32,720 --> 00:24:33,880
Alright, enough.

351
00:24:40,000 --> 00:24:42,160
So, are you going
to propose to Pakbung now?

352
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:47,120
There's still one more thing I need to do.

353
00:24:56,640 --> 00:24:58,440
I want to hire you.

354
00:24:58,960 --> 00:25:00,600
These are my mom's snacks.

355
00:25:00,680 --> 00:25:04,120
Normally, she sells them
through someone she knows,

356
00:25:04,200 --> 00:25:05,320
but I want to sell them online too.

357
00:25:06,520 --> 00:25:08,760
Have you tried doing a live stream yet?

358
00:25:09,480 --> 00:25:12,440
I tried last night,
but I didn't even get ten viewers.

359
00:25:13,240 --> 00:25:14,400
So,

360
00:25:14,480 --> 00:25:16,520
I wanted an expert like you to help.

361
00:25:18,040 --> 00:25:20,800
But I don't have much budget, Pakbung.

362
00:25:21,720 --> 00:25:24,640
How much do you charge?

363
00:25:27,040 --> 00:25:28,560
Can I taste them first?

364
00:25:28,640 --> 00:25:29,680
Of course.

365
00:25:32,280 --> 00:25:33,280
Here.

366
00:25:38,320 --> 00:25:39,320
How is it?

367
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:42,000
So good.

368
00:25:44,920 --> 00:25:46,040
How about this?

369
00:25:48,360 --> 00:25:50,320
I'll take two percent of revenue.

370
00:25:50,920 --> 00:25:53,160
If I sell a lot on live, I earn a lot.

371
00:25:53,240 --> 00:25:57,200
But if I can't sell,
you don't have to pay. Is that good?

372
00:25:58,400 --> 00:25:59,440
Really, Pakbung?

373
00:26:00,920 --> 00:26:04,560
I thought you'd be
more bloodsucking than this.

374
00:26:05,400 --> 00:26:06,320
Hey.

375
00:26:07,920 --> 00:26:10,000
Back then, yeah, maybe.

376
00:26:10,080 --> 00:26:12,520
But people can change, right?

377
00:26:15,080 --> 00:26:18,720
Well, is it because of Trai?

378
00:26:21,680 --> 00:26:24,400
When you get married, invite me too, okay?

379
00:26:25,120 --> 00:26:26,520
I want to,

380
00:26:26,600 --> 00:26:29,040
but I'm waiting for him to propose.

381
00:26:29,120 --> 00:26:31,720
Well, if Trai doesn't propose,

382
00:26:32,560 --> 00:26:34,360
then propose to him yourself.

383
00:26:35,760 --> 00:26:37,440
- Can I?
- Of course.

384
00:26:44,440 --> 00:26:46,120
Speak of the devil,
he's calling right now.

385
00:26:46,760 --> 00:26:47,800
Look.

386
00:26:50,040 --> 00:26:52,760
What could Trai want, calling me?

387
00:26:53,280 --> 00:26:54,240
Or…

388
00:26:55,040 --> 00:26:57,920
maybe he's calling
to set up a surprise proposal for you?

389
00:26:59,080 --> 00:26:59,880
Hey.

390
00:26:59,960 --> 00:27:02,800
You never know.

391
00:27:17,600 --> 00:27:19,640
These are the share transfer documents.

392
00:27:21,360 --> 00:27:23,600
I'm going to give you part of mine.

393
00:27:23,680 --> 00:27:25,640
Take a look and see
if anything doesn't look right.

394
00:27:31,640 --> 00:27:36,520
SHARE TRANSFER DOCUMENT

395
00:27:46,800 --> 00:27:48,040
Thank you, Trai.

396
00:27:49,120 --> 00:27:50,480
I've decided.

397
00:27:51,200 --> 00:27:52,760
I'd rather not take them.

398
00:27:57,240 --> 00:27:58,560
Why, Da?

399
00:27:59,280 --> 00:28:00,960
It's something you deserve.

400
00:28:01,800 --> 00:28:03,040
Be Rich,

401
00:28:03,960 --> 00:28:05,920
this house,

402
00:28:07,720 --> 00:28:10,160
all of this is
an embarrassing past for me.

403
00:28:10,240 --> 00:28:12,200
I really don't want to remember any of it.

404
00:28:13,360 --> 00:28:14,400
You understand me, right?

405
00:28:22,680 --> 00:28:24,920
Then if you need anything,
just tell this friend, alright?

406
00:28:26,320 --> 00:28:27,720
I'm always ready to help.

407
00:28:28,480 --> 00:28:29,920
Thanks, Trai.

408
00:28:30,880 --> 00:28:31,720
So, what's up today?

409
00:28:33,320 --> 00:28:34,240
I almost forgot.

410
00:28:36,400 --> 00:28:38,040
These are my mom's desserts.

411
00:28:40,560 --> 00:28:42,160
I'm going to sell them online too.

412
00:28:52,880 --> 00:28:54,680
I heard you're not taking
the shares in Be Rich?

413
00:29:05,080 --> 00:29:06,480
News travels fast, huh?

414
00:29:06,560 --> 00:29:08,480
How's your mom's illness?

415
00:29:09,120 --> 00:29:10,080
Does she not need treatment anymore?

416
00:29:10,840 --> 00:29:13,320
I've got some savings.

417
00:29:13,920 --> 00:29:15,120
Honestly,

418
00:29:16,000 --> 00:29:18,280
before this, I wasn't exactly struggling.

419
00:29:19,720 --> 00:29:20,720
I was just…

420
00:29:22,160 --> 00:29:23,000
a bit greedy.

421
00:29:23,680 --> 00:29:24,920
Aren't we all?

422
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:26,480
Since the time I was born,

423
00:29:26,560 --> 00:29:29,760
I feel like
I like myself the most right now.

424
00:29:32,400 --> 00:29:34,600
Have you ever tried
my mom's desserts, Mr. Rachen?

425
00:29:36,720 --> 00:29:37,920
Here.

426
00:29:38,600 --> 00:29:41,000
- Thank you.
- We also do catering, you know.

427
00:29:41,080 --> 00:29:43,040
If Be Rich has a party

428
00:29:43,120 --> 00:29:46,240
or a seminar, you can contact me anytime.

429
00:29:46,320 --> 00:29:47,480
- Okay.
- I'll give you a discount.

430
00:29:48,320 --> 00:29:49,240
Alright.

431
00:29:52,640 --> 00:29:53,480
Darin.

432
00:29:57,680 --> 00:29:58,600
Good luck.

433
00:30:00,880 --> 00:30:02,160
You too.

434
00:30:29,040 --> 00:30:31,960
Pakbung! Pakbung.

435
00:30:32,040 --> 00:30:35,080
I heard Mr. Trai got his shares back?

436
00:30:35,960 --> 00:30:38,120
- Yeah.
- Then why are you still doing this?

437
00:30:38,200 --> 00:30:39,600
Go get ready.

438
00:30:40,280 --> 00:30:41,520
Ready for what?

439
00:30:42,040 --> 00:30:44,440
I'm taking product photos for Ms. Darin.

440
00:30:45,640 --> 00:30:47,760
I'm gonna attach the listings
during the live stream tonight.

441
00:30:47,840 --> 00:30:49,240
Ugh, stop shooting already.

442
00:30:49,320 --> 00:30:51,920
Go dress up. Mr. Lee told me

443
00:30:52,000 --> 00:30:54,440
Mr. Trai's picking out a gift for you.

444
00:30:54,520 --> 00:30:56,280
I think, tonight,

445
00:30:56,360 --> 00:30:59,200
he's totally gonna propose!

446
00:31:02,840 --> 00:31:04,120
Propose? Tonight?

447
00:31:04,200 --> 00:31:05,920
Aha!

448
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:08,800
You do want to get married too, don't you?

449
00:31:12,400 --> 00:31:13,400
No.

450
00:31:14,720 --> 00:31:16,000
I don't want to get married.

451
00:31:18,960 --> 00:31:20,200
Really?

452
00:31:20,280 --> 00:31:22,240
Bung! Bung!

453
00:31:22,760 --> 00:31:24,080
A delivery from Trai.

454
00:31:24,160 --> 00:31:25,360
- Huh?
- Yeah.

455
00:31:34,520 --> 00:31:36,080
MR. TRAI

456
00:31:36,160 --> 00:31:38,240
<i>Did you get it yet? See you this evening.</i>

457
00:31:41,520 --> 00:31:43,920
See? See?

458
00:31:44,520 --> 00:31:46,720
With that kind of box,

459
00:31:46,800 --> 00:31:50,680
this is definitely
a beautiful dinner outfit.

460
00:31:50,760 --> 00:31:52,040
Hey, wait.

461
00:31:53,760 --> 00:31:55,920
Is my friend
really about to get a husband?

462
00:31:57,760 --> 00:32:00,000
- Hey, open it.
- Open it. Bung, open it.

463
00:32:00,080 --> 00:32:01,680
- Open it. Open it.
- Here.

464
00:32:01,760 --> 00:32:02,680
Hey, wait.

465
00:32:02,760 --> 00:32:04,160
Can I film it?

466
00:32:04,240 --> 00:32:06,680
Before you open it, can I it?
I wanna make content.

467
00:32:06,760 --> 00:32:08,160
Come on, Bung.

468
00:32:08,240 --> 00:32:10,080
Hold on. Alright.

469
00:32:10,160 --> 00:32:12,440
- Go ahead.
- Hold on.

470
00:32:13,800 --> 00:32:15,200
I'll do the sound effects.

471
00:32:31,640 --> 00:32:32,800
Grilled intestines?

472
00:32:39,240 --> 00:32:40,920
Bung, your call.

473
00:32:47,400 --> 00:32:50,240
Oh? It's our favorite grilled intestines.
You don't like it?

474
00:32:50,320 --> 00:32:52,720
This is the gift

475
00:32:52,800 --> 00:32:55,200
you really meant to send me? Seriously?

476
00:32:57,320 --> 00:33:00,600
Hey, I had Lee get in line this morning.
If it was any later, it'd be sold out.

477
00:33:01,200 --> 00:33:03,200
Save some for me too.
I'll come eat it with you this evening.

478
00:33:07,360 --> 00:33:09,480
Besides grilled intestines,

479
00:33:09,560 --> 00:33:11,080
do you have anything else?

480
00:33:15,240 --> 00:33:16,880
Oh, papaya salad
with crab and fermented fish?

481
00:33:17,560 --> 00:33:19,200
You want papaya salad
with crab and fermented fish?

482
00:33:20,360 --> 00:33:22,400
Besides the papaya salad
with crab and fermented fish?

483
00:33:22,480 --> 00:33:25,320
Besides that? Oh! Bubble milk tea.

484
00:33:31,960 --> 00:33:33,280
I gotta go, Mr. Trai.

485
00:33:43,640 --> 00:33:46,800
Sorry, girl. I thought he'd propose today.

486
00:33:46,880 --> 00:33:47,720
Yeah.

487
00:33:47,800 --> 00:33:49,960
But the grilled intestines are delicious.

488
00:33:51,360 --> 00:33:52,600
But it's fine.

489
00:33:52,680 --> 00:33:54,280
You don't even want to get married, right?

490
00:33:54,360 --> 00:33:56,160
- Yeah. Right.
- I do.

491
00:33:57,160 --> 00:33:57,960
What?

492
00:33:58,040 --> 00:33:59,880
I wanna get married!

493
00:34:09,560 --> 00:34:10,520
Eat some.

494
00:34:10,600 --> 00:34:11,639
Eat.

495
00:34:12,920 --> 00:34:14,639
Don't be grumpy.
Eat grilled intestines first.

496
00:34:17,360 --> 00:34:19,480
- He didn't propose, so eat this first.
- Cucumber?

497
00:34:24,239 --> 00:34:27,080
What's wrong?
You've been quiet all evening.

498
00:34:28,280 --> 00:34:29,920
Were the grilled intestines not tasty?

499
00:34:31,280 --> 00:34:34,320
Be Rich is settled.

500
00:34:34,840 --> 00:34:36,440
And

501
00:34:36,960 --> 00:34:40,159
the school's fine too.

502
00:34:41,040 --> 00:34:43,520
And then…

503
00:34:43,600 --> 00:34:45,400
And then?

504
00:34:45,480 --> 00:34:48,280
- And then…
- And…

505
00:34:50,320 --> 00:34:51,800
What is it? You can tell me.

506
00:34:55,639 --> 00:34:57,880
If Trai doesn't propose,

507
00:34:57,960 --> 00:34:59,760
then propose to him yourself.

508
00:35:01,000 --> 00:35:03,240
Mr. Trai, I think we should…

509
00:35:03,320 --> 00:35:06,080
- We… We should what?
- Uh…

510
00:35:07,160 --> 00:35:11,040
- I think we…
- We should what?

511
00:35:12,400 --> 00:35:14,600
- We…
- We should go on a trip.

512
00:35:58,120 --> 00:36:00,360
We're here!

513
00:36:00,440 --> 00:36:01,680
Hey. I think…

514
00:36:01,760 --> 00:36:03,600
I think I can smell the sea already.

515
00:36:04,720 --> 00:36:06,440
Let's go.

516
00:36:06,520 --> 00:36:08,560
- Sea.
- Go, go.

517
00:36:10,000 --> 00:36:11,400
Where's the beach?

518
00:36:11,920 --> 00:36:13,120
I don't know.

519
00:36:14,480 --> 00:36:15,280
‪Hey, look.

520
00:36:15,360 --> 00:36:17,000
Welcome to Ravindra.

521
00:36:17,080 --> 00:36:19,000
- Hello.
- Thank you.

522
00:36:21,840 --> 00:36:23,240
Hey.

523
00:36:23,320 --> 00:36:26,200
I'm gonna go take some check-in photos
by the beach and post a story.

524
00:36:26,280 --> 00:36:28,440
- Yeah, let's go.
- Wait.

525
00:36:29,120 --> 00:36:32,320
Did you forget why we came to the beach?

526
00:36:33,200 --> 00:36:34,280
Why did we come?

527
00:36:36,040 --> 00:36:39,480
Well…

528
00:36:40,640 --> 00:36:42,600
We came to celebrate your birthday.

529
00:36:42,680 --> 00:36:44,480
How could you forget?

530
00:36:46,560 --> 00:36:48,480
I told you.

531
00:36:48,560 --> 00:36:51,480
Once the school opens,
we won't have time anymore.

532
00:36:52,000 --> 00:36:53,280
So we had to come now.

533
00:36:53,360 --> 00:36:55,240
Oh, yeah?

534
00:36:55,320 --> 00:36:58,240
I saw you whispering
with Samlee and Niuniu, so I thought

535
00:36:58,320 --> 00:37:00,520
maybe there was something
a bit more special than that?

536
00:37:01,560 --> 00:37:02,760
No.

537
00:37:02,840 --> 00:37:04,320
No?

538
00:37:04,400 --> 00:37:06,000
Just celebrating your birthday

539
00:37:06,080 --> 00:37:08,880
is already the most special thing ever.

540
00:37:08,960 --> 00:37:09,800
Right?

541
00:37:11,080 --> 00:37:12,200
Yeah.

542
00:37:13,160 --> 00:37:14,160
Let's go.

543
00:37:14,240 --> 00:37:16,160
- Let's go.
- Yeah. Let's go.

544
00:37:16,240 --> 00:37:17,080
Wait.

545
00:37:17,640 --> 00:37:20,000
The beach is that way.

546
00:37:21,640 --> 00:37:23,280
Oh, wrong way.

547
00:37:31,320 --> 00:37:33,320
This is the cake the hotel prepared.

548
00:37:33,400 --> 00:37:36,160
And this is the proposal card.

549
00:37:40,520 --> 00:37:42,960
I'll roll it up first.

550
00:37:43,480 --> 00:37:47,000
Then stick it in like this.

551
00:37:49,880 --> 00:37:52,400
Are you guys sure
this won't get stuck in Mr. Trai's throat?

552
00:37:52,480 --> 00:37:54,680
He's not gonna shove the whole cake
into his mouth.

553
00:37:54,760 --> 00:37:55,640
- Yeah.
- He'll

554
00:37:55,720 --> 00:37:59,520
scoop it slowly then find it.

555
00:38:02,760 --> 00:38:07,560
Wait. So, where do we hide the cake
so Mr. Trai doesn't see it first?

556
00:38:08,160 --> 00:38:08,920
Good point.

557
00:38:09,000 --> 00:38:11,000
Pakbung. Pakbung.

558
00:38:12,840 --> 00:38:14,760
Hey, what do we do?

559
00:38:16,520 --> 00:38:18,400
What do we do?

560
00:38:30,800 --> 00:38:31,840
What are you guys doing?

561
00:38:34,920 --> 00:38:36,040
I was just thinking about you.

562
00:38:36,120 --> 00:38:37,760
Thinking about me?

563
00:38:39,760 --> 00:38:40,720
That's weird.

564
00:38:40,800 --> 00:38:43,320
Why does today suddenly feel…

565
00:38:47,360 --> 00:38:48,920
so sweet?

566
00:38:50,440 --> 00:38:51,440
Is something up?

567
00:38:53,040 --> 00:38:53,960
Hey.

568
00:38:57,640 --> 00:38:58,920
Nothing.

569
00:39:00,000 --> 00:39:01,280
What could there be?

570
00:39:03,840 --> 00:39:04,880
Hey.

571
00:39:04,960 --> 00:39:07,960
Mr. Trai, you brought a camera, right?

572
00:39:08,040 --> 00:39:10,800
You're gonna take pictures
with Pakbung, right?

573
00:39:10,880 --> 00:39:12,120
Yeah, go.

574
00:39:12,200 --> 00:39:13,600
Go take pictures.

575
00:39:13,680 --> 00:39:15,000
Go, go.

576
00:39:15,080 --> 00:39:18,200
- Go. Go take pictures.
- Take good pictures.

577
00:39:33,560 --> 00:39:35,480
What's wrong? Why do you look so grumpy?

578
00:39:37,080 --> 00:39:38,560
Grumpy? How?

579
00:39:44,480 --> 00:39:46,880
Turn here. Look at the camera.
One, two, three.

580
00:39:46,960 --> 00:39:48,160
Mm.

581
00:39:51,200 --> 00:39:52,280
See? Grumpy like this.

582
00:39:52,920 --> 00:39:53,960
Hey!

583
00:39:55,360 --> 00:39:57,360
That's not pretty at all. Delete it.

584
00:39:58,320 --> 00:40:00,000
Okay. I'll take
a really pretty one for you.

585
00:40:00,080 --> 00:40:00,960
Okay?

586
00:40:03,080 --> 00:40:05,680
Go stand over there. There.

587
00:40:09,120 --> 00:40:10,200
Good.

588
00:40:11,720 --> 00:40:13,960
Smile, smile.

589
00:40:14,040 --> 00:40:15,880
Not a grimace. Smile.

590
00:40:17,960 --> 00:40:19,960
That's it. One, two, three.

591
00:40:22,960 --> 00:40:24,840
I think you should stand here instead.

592
00:40:24,920 --> 00:40:25,920
Better view.

593
00:40:27,080 --> 00:40:27,960
Come on.

594
00:40:29,560 --> 00:40:30,800
Alright.

595
00:40:30,880 --> 00:40:32,920
- Smile.
- Flick my hair too?

596
00:40:33,000 --> 00:40:34,160
Smile.

597
00:40:34,240 --> 00:40:35,880
One, two, three. Go.

598
00:40:35,960 --> 00:40:37,440
One, two, three.

599
00:40:38,200 --> 00:40:39,040
One more.

600
00:40:47,040 --> 00:40:48,000
What are you laughing at?

601
00:40:50,680 --> 00:40:51,840
Whose girlfriend is this?

602
00:40:52,920 --> 00:40:54,240
So damn cute.

603
00:40:57,320 --> 00:40:58,320
Look.

604
00:41:03,480 --> 00:41:05,000
Stop flattering me.

605
00:41:05,640 --> 00:41:06,880
Come here. I'll take one of you.

606
00:41:06,960 --> 00:41:08,480
I think we should take it together.

607
00:41:10,160 --> 00:41:11,080
Here.

608
00:41:13,320 --> 00:41:15,040
Okay.

609
00:41:17,440 --> 00:41:18,680
Ready?

610
00:41:19,280 --> 00:41:21,200
One, two, three.

611
00:41:21,280 --> 00:41:23,000
One, two, three.

612
00:41:23,520 --> 00:41:25,080
One, two, three.

613
00:41:28,040 --> 00:41:29,400
Let's see.

614
00:41:41,000 --> 00:41:42,600
Look.

615
00:41:43,800 --> 00:41:46,760
BE MY WIFE

616
00:41:51,800 --> 00:41:53,280
Where's the "Will you marry me?"?

617
00:41:53,360 --> 00:41:56,960
Uh… well… I didn't know how to write it.

618
00:41:57,040 --> 00:41:59,200
Oh, the word "me".

619
00:41:59,280 --> 00:42:01,080
I'm sorry, Mr. Trai!

620
00:42:01,160 --> 00:42:03,440
Lee! Prarop! You two.

621
00:42:06,120 --> 00:42:07,560
You did so well.

622
00:42:07,640 --> 00:42:10,600
This is amazing. This is exactly
what I've been waiting for.

623
00:42:18,960 --> 00:42:20,400
"Be my wife."

624
00:42:23,440 --> 00:42:24,400
Hey.

625
00:42:25,360 --> 00:42:26,760
Will you marry me, Pakbung?

626
00:42:27,360 --> 00:42:29,560
You're proposing to me?

627
00:42:30,200 --> 00:42:31,840
Just like
how you wanted to propose to me too.

628
00:42:33,840 --> 00:42:34,680
You knew?

629
00:42:36,640 --> 00:42:38,200
Did you layer my plan with yours?

630
00:42:39,560 --> 00:42:42,120
You asked me to be your boyfriend,
so it's only fair I propose.

631
00:42:45,160 --> 00:42:47,760
Pakbung, will you marry me?

632
00:42:51,720 --> 00:42:53,560
Yes! I will!

633
00:42:53,640 --> 00:42:55,840
Of course, I will. Why not?

634
00:42:58,720 --> 00:43:01,320
Put it on. Put it on.

635
00:43:03,040 --> 00:43:04,320
Mr. Trai!

636
00:43:06,440 --> 00:43:07,560
Hey, left hand.

637
00:43:08,560 --> 00:43:10,320
Oops, I forgot.

638
00:43:11,440 --> 00:43:12,600
Left hand. Here.

639
00:43:24,120 --> 00:43:25,280
My hand's shaking.

640
00:43:27,000 --> 00:43:28,560
It's really shaking.

641
00:43:28,640 --> 00:43:29,880
Thank you, Pakbung,

642
00:43:31,160 --> 00:43:32,360
for letting me love you.

643
00:43:32,960 --> 00:43:35,600
I'm lucky to get to love you too.

644
00:43:50,560 --> 00:43:53,080
My friend's got a husband now!

645
00:43:58,440 --> 00:44:00,360
Seizing the moment, aren't you?

646
00:44:02,080 --> 00:44:03,600
How long had you planned this for?

647
00:44:03,680 --> 00:44:05,040
For a while.

648
00:44:05,120 --> 00:44:07,520
At first, I wasn't sure
if you wanted to marry me,

649
00:44:07,600 --> 00:44:09,560
so I sent the grilled intestines to test.

650
00:44:12,760 --> 00:44:14,200
That was part of your plan too?

651
00:44:16,000 --> 00:44:17,800
As soon as you said
you wanted to get married,

652
00:44:17,880 --> 00:44:20,120
I told Mr. Lee immediately.

653
00:44:22,640 --> 00:44:24,520
So you guys knew too?

654
00:44:25,480 --> 00:44:29,280
Oh, so you were pretending
not to know about the cake?

655
00:44:29,360 --> 00:44:30,440
That was an act?

656
00:44:31,040 --> 00:44:34,600
Well, we were afraid you'd propose first
and steal Mr. Trai's moment.

657
00:44:35,200 --> 00:44:37,280
But I ate the paper!

658
00:44:38,080 --> 00:44:39,320
That was evil.

659
00:44:41,520 --> 00:44:43,160
- You wanted a husband, didn't you?
- Calm down.

660
00:44:43,240 --> 00:44:45,800
- Calm down.
- You wanted a husband.

661
00:44:56,000 --> 00:44:58,800
There's actually more than this.

662
00:45:04,640 --> 00:45:07,680
- Wow.
- Hold it properly.

663
00:45:08,320 --> 00:45:09,920
Oh, my.

664
00:45:10,720 --> 00:45:13,560
- Hold it properly. You'll ruin my shirt.
- You won't let me hold your hand.

665
00:45:14,160 --> 00:45:15,240
My shirt.

666
00:45:16,760 --> 00:45:18,760
Walking back holding hands like that,

667
00:45:18,840 --> 00:45:21,280
don't tell me you actually agreed
to marry Trai already.

668
00:45:24,720 --> 00:45:25,800
Just call me your brother-in-law.

669
00:45:28,480 --> 00:45:30,880
Then you have to call me
your father-in-law.

670
00:45:34,040 --> 00:45:34,960
Come on.

671
00:45:35,040 --> 00:45:36,960
- Let's go.
- Go.

672
00:45:37,040 --> 00:45:39,280
- Pakbung.
- Yes?

673
00:45:39,880 --> 00:45:42,880
You're fabulous.
Totally worthy of being my daughter.

674
00:45:44,000 --> 00:45:45,600
Mr. Trai,

675
00:45:45,680 --> 00:45:48,240
I prepared the celebration party

676
00:45:48,320 --> 00:45:50,560
exactly as you requested,
every single detail.

677
00:45:50,640 --> 00:45:53,960
And when the wedding day comes,

678
00:45:54,040 --> 00:45:55,560
don't forget to use
my services again, okay?

679
00:45:55,640 --> 00:45:56,520
Of course.

680
00:45:56,600 --> 00:45:58,320
Thank you!

681
00:45:58,400 --> 00:45:59,720
Everyone, help me set things up.

682
00:45:59,800 --> 00:46:01,280
Okay, okay. Let's go.

683
00:46:01,360 --> 00:46:03,200
- The guys carry the heavy stuff.
- Okay.

684
00:46:03,280 --> 00:46:05,240
Take this.

685
00:46:06,040 --> 00:46:07,640
- I'll take the plates.
- Hey.

686
00:46:08,160 --> 00:46:09,320
You brought everyone here?

687
00:46:10,280 --> 00:46:12,840
It's an important day for us.
Of course I had to bring our family.

688
00:46:12,920 --> 00:46:14,400
Damn, Trai.

689
00:46:14,480 --> 00:46:17,360
Isn't this a bit much? Listen to yourself.

690
00:46:17,440 --> 00:46:18,840
You know what?

691
00:46:18,920 --> 00:46:22,160
I canceled a meeting
just to come celebrate you two.

692
00:46:22,240 --> 00:46:24,200
Oh, stop complaining.

693
00:46:24,280 --> 00:46:26,640
Seriously, if I hadn't invited you,
would you have been upset?

694
00:46:27,640 --> 00:46:28,480
Listen to you.

695
00:46:28,560 --> 00:46:31,840
Pakbung, are you sure you want this guy?
Look at that mouth of his.

696
00:46:34,240 --> 00:46:36,840
And do you have
any better offer for me, Mr. Rachen?

697
00:46:41,240 --> 00:46:42,680
How about 100 million?
I can transfer it right now.

698
00:46:45,080 --> 00:46:46,280
Only 100 million?

699
00:46:47,960 --> 00:46:50,040
If it's 10 billion, then we can talk.

700
00:46:51,240 --> 00:46:52,040
Right?

701
00:46:52,800 --> 00:46:54,760
You've leveled up, Pakbung.

702
00:46:54,840 --> 00:46:57,040
You're ruthless now.

703
00:46:58,120 --> 00:46:59,760
Trai's my beloved little brother.

704
00:47:01,040 --> 00:47:03,680
And you are like my little sister.

705
00:47:05,040 --> 00:47:06,600
If Trai

706
00:47:06,680 --> 00:47:08,200
ever makes you cry,

707
00:47:08,280 --> 00:47:09,560
come tell me right away.

708
00:47:10,320 --> 00:47:12,440
- I won't let him off.
- Wow.

709
00:47:13,280 --> 00:47:15,000
And if Pakbung makes me cry? Like this.

710
00:47:20,040 --> 00:47:21,640
If she makes you cry?

711
00:47:21,720 --> 00:47:23,080
Then I'll laugh at you.

712
00:47:23,840 --> 00:47:26,920
Seeing you cry is so satisfying.

713
00:47:27,000 --> 00:47:28,920
Look at your crying face.

714
00:47:29,000 --> 00:47:30,400
You're such a jerk.

715
00:47:31,160 --> 00:47:32,840
Did you just insult me?

716
00:47:37,480 --> 00:47:38,560
I love you.

717
00:47:38,640 --> 00:47:40,560
- I love you too.
- Congratulations.

718
00:47:41,200 --> 00:47:42,120
Thank you.

719
00:47:59,880 --> 00:48:01,120
How is it?

720
00:48:10,360 --> 00:48:12,040
You knew Mr. Trai's plan.
Why didn't you tell me?

721
00:48:13,520 --> 00:48:15,320
If we told you,
it wouldn't have been a surprise.

722
00:48:15,400 --> 00:48:17,040
- Yeah. Right.
- Right?

723
00:48:17,920 --> 00:48:19,800
You're talking back now?

724
00:48:22,160 --> 00:48:24,320
Hey, from now on,

725
00:48:24,400 --> 00:48:25,880
you have to behave, okay?

726
00:48:25,960 --> 00:48:27,160
When you're with Trai,

727
00:48:27,240 --> 00:48:30,520
you can't be all bossy and shouty
and aggressive like you were with me.

728
00:48:30,600 --> 00:48:32,000
Got it?

729
00:48:32,880 --> 00:48:34,560
Dad's right here.

730
00:48:34,640 --> 00:48:36,920
Are you trying to be my second dad now?

731
00:48:37,000 --> 00:48:38,760
I'm just saying.

732
00:48:39,800 --> 00:48:41,200
But if you ever feel uncomfortable,

733
00:48:41,280 --> 00:48:43,200
or if you're stressed,
or if you wanna yell at someone,

734
00:48:43,280 --> 00:48:44,360
come back, okay?

735
00:48:44,440 --> 00:48:45,440
I'll listen to you.

736
00:48:46,680 --> 00:48:48,640
Don't talk like
we won't be together anymore.

737
00:48:54,160 --> 00:48:55,680
Marriage, Pakbung,

738
00:48:55,760 --> 00:48:57,680
is like

739
00:48:57,760 --> 00:48:59,560
starting a new chapter.

740
00:48:59,640 --> 00:49:02,000
You'll have to move in with Mr. Trai.

741
00:49:02,080 --> 00:49:05,600
Things won't be the same.

742
00:49:06,680 --> 00:49:08,600
And some things will have to change.

743
00:49:08,680 --> 00:49:10,040
Even me,

744
00:49:10,640 --> 00:49:12,880
I only just moved in
with you not long ago,

745
00:49:12,960 --> 00:49:14,800
and I'm already feeling
that ache in my chest.

746
00:49:15,880 --> 00:49:17,720
Kanah probably feels it even more.

747
00:49:17,800 --> 00:49:18,920
Are you

748
00:49:19,720 --> 00:49:20,960
gonna be lonely?

749
00:49:22,600 --> 00:49:23,800
Lonely? Come on.

750
00:49:23,880 --> 00:49:26,920
Next year, I'll have hospital duty.
I'll be stuck at the hospital.

751
00:49:27,000 --> 00:49:29,600
I won't even come home.
When would I even have time to be lonely?

752
00:49:29,680 --> 00:49:31,240
Kanah…

753
00:49:31,320 --> 00:49:33,720
I don't want to leave you.

754
00:49:36,280 --> 00:49:39,640
Hey. Then, don't marry Trai.

755
00:49:41,040 --> 00:49:42,080
No.

756
00:49:44,640 --> 00:49:45,360
Right.

757
00:49:46,480 --> 00:49:48,440
- That's a big one.
- The grilled shrimp is here.

758
00:49:51,320 --> 00:49:53,600
The barbecue needs a minute,
waiting on the grill.

759
00:49:54,560 --> 00:49:56,800
- Got it.
- Thank you, Mr. Trai.

760
00:49:58,520 --> 00:50:00,120
He's more important than me now?

761
00:50:01,880 --> 00:50:03,920
Don't. Don't try to bribe me with shrimp.

762
00:50:04,000 --> 00:50:05,560
I'm not bribing you.

763
00:50:05,640 --> 00:50:07,480
I'm giving it to you
so you can peel it for me.

764
00:50:08,480 --> 00:50:09,760
Soon, we won't be living together,

765
00:50:09,840 --> 00:50:12,800
so take good care
of your gorgeous sister for once.

766
00:50:15,760 --> 00:50:18,200
Yes, ma'am. Gorgeous.
You're the most gorgeous,

767
00:50:18,280 --> 00:50:20,080
- Bung.
- You're the cutest.

768
00:50:20,160 --> 00:50:21,800
Ouch, it's hot.

769
00:50:22,920 --> 00:50:24,120
- Peel it for me, please.
- Yes, ma'am.

770
00:50:24,200 --> 00:50:25,600
- Mr. Trai.
- Yes?

771
00:50:26,280 --> 00:50:29,240
Well, I know

772
00:50:29,320 --> 00:50:31,280
you can take care
of Pakbung better than I ever could.

773
00:50:32,800 --> 00:50:34,280
But…

774
00:50:34,360 --> 00:50:35,800
still…

775
00:50:36,920 --> 00:50:38,080
please take care of my daughter.

776
00:50:39,960 --> 00:50:43,720
Yes. I'll take care
of Pakbung with my life.

777
00:50:48,400 --> 00:50:50,200
Pakbung and you

778
00:50:50,840 --> 00:50:52,800
are lucky to have found each other

779
00:50:53,400 --> 00:50:54,360
and to get to love each other.

780
00:50:55,880 --> 00:50:57,520
But after this…

781
00:50:57,600 --> 00:50:58,600
It's hot.

782
00:50:58,680 --> 00:51:00,520
life may be harder.

783
00:51:01,480 --> 00:51:03,880
Some things might have to change.

784
00:51:07,520 --> 00:51:09,840
But I want the two of you…

785
00:51:14,480 --> 00:51:16,080
to keep holding hands.

786
00:51:16,840 --> 00:51:18,800
Remember the feeling from the first day

787
00:51:18,880 --> 00:51:20,360
you fell in love.

788
00:51:21,800 --> 00:51:23,200
May your love never change.

789
00:51:39,320 --> 00:51:40,360
Come here.

790
00:51:40,440 --> 00:51:42,280
Pose for a picture.

791
00:51:42,360 --> 00:51:43,680
Snap.

792
00:51:43,760 --> 00:51:44,880
One more.

793
00:51:46,960 --> 00:51:48,480
Alright, cheers.

794
00:51:48,560 --> 00:51:50,040
Cheers.

795
00:51:50,120 --> 00:51:51,320
Trai, cheers.

796
00:51:51,400 --> 00:51:53,120
Cheers from here.

797
00:51:58,520 --> 00:51:59,880
That was kinda loud.

798
00:51:59,960 --> 00:52:01,640
Lee, you're unbelievable.

799
00:52:02,880 --> 00:52:05,400
There's still no barbecue yet.
I'll go grill some for you.

800
00:52:08,000 --> 00:52:09,520
Kanah, I want some too.

801
00:52:09,600 --> 00:52:10,800
That's enough, Bung.

802
00:52:10,880 --> 00:52:11,720
So good.

803
00:52:11,800 --> 00:52:13,640
- Are you being nosy?
- No.

804
00:52:13,720 --> 00:52:17,000
- No, no.
- Oh, really?

805
00:52:17,720 --> 00:52:19,520
- No.
- I didn't have even one.

806
00:52:19,600 --> 00:52:20,920
Want another one?

807
00:52:21,000 --> 00:52:22,960
- Enough.
- Are you telling me to get lost?

808
00:52:23,040 --> 00:52:24,720
- Yeah.
- I'll grill. You go sit down.

809
00:52:24,800 --> 00:52:27,040
Oh, it's okay.

810
00:52:27,120 --> 00:52:29,000
I like taking care of people.

811
00:52:30,200 --> 00:52:31,800
Add the score.

812
00:52:31,880 --> 00:52:33,120
- Add the score?
- Yeah.

813
00:52:33,200 --> 00:52:35,560
If you like taking care
of others that much,

814
00:52:36,080 --> 00:52:37,520
don't you want someone
to take care of you?

815
00:52:43,360 --> 00:52:46,000
If you like me, eat it.
If you don't, just walk away.

816
00:52:52,640 --> 00:52:54,560
Then don't eat it.

817
00:52:54,640 --> 00:52:55,880
I'll eat it.

818
00:53:00,800 --> 00:53:02,240
What?

819
00:53:02,320 --> 00:53:04,800
I thought you said you were just friends?

820
00:53:05,400 --> 00:53:08,240
There's feeding too?

821
00:53:09,360 --> 00:53:11,400
They're moving faster than us.

822
00:53:12,760 --> 00:53:13,840
You want to eat it?

823
00:53:14,440 --> 00:53:15,600
I want someone to feed me.

824
00:53:19,640 --> 00:53:21,320
Here.

825
00:53:23,560 --> 00:53:24,480
Ow, hot, hot!

826
00:53:25,000 --> 00:53:27,640
- Hot!
- I'm sorry.

827
00:53:27,720 --> 00:53:29,040
Blow on it first.

828
00:53:30,080 --> 00:53:30,880
This one is raw.

829
00:53:30,960 --> 00:53:31,920
Blow on it.

830
00:53:34,400 --> 00:53:35,560
- So annoying.
- Do you hate me?

831
00:53:37,880 --> 00:53:39,080
That's nice.

832
00:53:39,160 --> 00:53:41,440
- Hey, this one's done, right?
- Yeah.

833
00:53:41,520 --> 00:53:42,800
Then I'll go serve it.

834
00:53:42,880 --> 00:53:43,800
- Okay.
- Take this.

835
00:53:43,880 --> 00:53:46,120
- This one again?
- It'll cool down soon.

836
00:53:48,920 --> 00:53:49,920
Whoa, there are crabs here!

837
00:53:52,320 --> 00:53:54,240
- Be careful.
- Hey.

838
00:54:05,280 --> 00:54:06,320
It feels like a dream,

839
00:54:06,920 --> 00:54:08,080
being here like this.

840
00:54:09,400 --> 00:54:10,840
A dream?

841
00:54:11,440 --> 00:54:14,080
I'm still stuffed.

842
00:54:14,760 --> 00:54:17,920
We ran off
instead of just walking normally.

843
00:54:18,680 --> 00:54:21,480
Hey. Can't you let me
be romantic for once?

844
00:54:23,960 --> 00:54:25,080
Let's try again.

845
00:54:36,200 --> 00:54:37,840
There are so many stars here.

846
00:54:40,600 --> 00:54:44,440
Which ones are your family?

847
00:54:46,800 --> 00:54:49,280
That one. Those two.

848
00:54:50,160 --> 00:54:51,880
See? One, two.

849
00:54:54,280 --> 00:54:57,680
Hello, Ms. Duangdao, Mr. Tritot!

850
00:54:58,600 --> 00:54:59,880
So formal.

851
00:55:00,480 --> 00:55:02,200
You should call them Dad and Mom.

852
00:55:04,320 --> 00:55:05,840
Dad, Mom,

853
00:55:05,920 --> 00:55:07,920
hello.

854
00:55:08,000 --> 00:55:09,800
It's me, Pakbung.

855
00:55:10,560 --> 00:55:11,640
Right now,

856
00:55:12,360 --> 00:55:13,960
your son

857
00:55:14,040 --> 00:55:15,840
is in my hands.

858
00:55:21,280 --> 00:55:22,560
Don't worry.

859
00:55:22,640 --> 00:55:24,600
I'll take good care of him.

860
00:55:25,480 --> 00:55:28,440
I won't let him feel lonely or isolated.

861
00:55:28,520 --> 00:55:30,280
I'll make him know that

862
00:55:30,360 --> 00:55:32,520
no matter what happens,

863
00:55:34,440 --> 00:55:35,920
I'll stay right here.

864
00:55:36,000 --> 00:55:38,000
I'll hold his hand.

865
00:55:43,440 --> 00:55:45,040
I'll be his family,

866
00:55:45,120 --> 00:55:47,080
his safe space,

867
00:55:47,640 --> 00:55:49,440
and the person who always believes in him.

868
00:55:53,120 --> 00:55:54,120
I'll be the same for her.

869
00:55:57,760 --> 00:55:59,640
I'll be her support

870
00:55:59,720 --> 00:56:01,320
and her shelter.

871
00:56:01,400 --> 00:56:04,000
I'll hold her hand on her happiest days

872
00:56:04,600 --> 00:56:06,080
and on her tearful ones.

873
00:56:07,840 --> 00:56:10,320
I'll be everything Pakbung wants me to be.

874
00:56:12,080 --> 00:56:14,080
That was better than mine.

875
00:56:15,240 --> 00:56:17,360
Then I'll be a star,

876
00:56:17,440 --> 00:56:19,680
guiding you with my light.

877
00:56:21,960 --> 00:56:25,160
Then I'll be bubble tea,
your energy boost. How's that?

878
00:56:25,240 --> 00:56:27,120
Then I'll be BBQ,

879
00:56:27,200 --> 00:56:28,720
healing your heart.

880
00:56:28,800 --> 00:56:32,000
Then I'll be grilled intestines,
your favorite.

881
00:56:32,640 --> 00:56:33,880
So you'll crave me every day.

882
00:56:37,360 --> 00:56:40,560
Then I'll be your fixed deposit account.

883
00:56:40,640 --> 00:56:43,120
I'll keep money for you.

884
00:56:43,200 --> 00:56:44,960
Wow, a fixed deposit?

885
00:56:46,000 --> 00:56:48,760
Then I'll be…

886
00:56:49,360 --> 00:56:50,440
You're stuck now?

887
00:56:51,200 --> 00:56:52,040
Can you think of anything?

888
00:56:52,120 --> 00:56:54,120
You can't, right?

889
00:56:55,560 --> 00:56:57,640
Then I'll just be Trai,

890
00:56:58,960 --> 00:57:00,680
the same man who loves you like this.

891
00:57:00,760 --> 00:57:01,600
And I'll never change.

892
00:57:45,960 --> 00:57:49,440
THE END

893
00:58:36,960 --> 00:58:39,440
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
